# Dependency Injection, Storage, and Routing

## GetIt — registration lifetimes

| Type | Registration | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Cubit | `registerFactory` | Fresh instance per page/provider |
| Repository / DataSource | `registerLazySingleton` | One instance, created on first use |
| SessionManager / Dio | `registerLazySingleton` | One instance, created on first use |
| SharedPreferences | `registerSingleton` | Eagerly initialized in `_registerCore` |

Global accessor: `injector` from `service_locator.dart`.

Always resolve via `injector<T>()` — never instantiate a registered type with `MyClass()`.

## Per-feature module pattern

```dart
// lib/core/di/modules/user_module.dart
class UserModule {
  static void register() {
    injector.registerLazySingleton(
      () => UserDataSource(dio: injector<Dio>()),
    );
    injector.registerLazySingleton(
      () => UserRepository(dataSource: injector<UserDataSource>()),
    );
    injector.registerFactory(
      () => GetUserCubit(repository: injector<UserRepository>()),
    );
  }
}
```

Call `UserModule.register()` from `ServiceLocator.injectDependencies()`.

## Local storage — which class to use

| Data | Class | Backend |
|---|---|---|
| Tokens, user JSON (sensitive) | `SessionManager` | `FlutterSecureStorage` |
| Feature flags, locale, onboarding | `LocalDataSource` | `SharedPreferences` |

`LocalDataSource` is constructor-injected with a `SharedPreferences` instance — no `init()` call needed.

A Cubit may inject `SessionManager` directly **only** for session lifecycle (sign-in / logout). All other data goes through a Repository.

## Routing — GoRouter

```dart
// Add name constant
class AppRoutes {
  static const String userProfile = 'user_profile';
}

// Add GoRoute in AppRouter.goRouter
GoRoute(
  path: '/${AppRoutes.userProfile}',
  name: AppRoutes.userProfile,
  builder: (_, __) => const UserProfilePage(),
),

// Navigate
context.goNamed(AppRoutes.userProfile);
```

- Never create a second `GlobalKey<NavigatorState>` — use `AppRouter.navigatorKey`.
